subsection.p:
In partial pivoting, we consider the magnitude of elements in the column before selecting a pivot element. The unpivoted row containing an element of maximum magnitude in a column is first swapped with the pivot row, and then the elimination step for that row proceeds. Consider the augmented matrix in  once again. In each step, the column entry of maximum magnitude is underlined for easy location, and then (if necessary) swapped into the correct location. Once the largest element is in the pivot position, we'll use the elimination step of sending all column values beneath the pivot to 0.

    \left[\begin{array}{3} 1 \amp  3 \amp  -13 \amp  -18 \\ 1 \amp  2 \amp  -10 \amp  -15\\ \mathbf{\underline{-6}} \amp  -7 \amp  46 \amp  77
\end{array} \right]
	\xto{R_1:R_3}
	\amp \left[\begin{array}{3} -6 \amp  -7 \amp  46 \amp  77 \\ 1 \amp  2 \amp  -10 \amp  -15 \\ 1 \amp  3 \amp  -13 \amp  -18
\end{array} \right]
	\xrightarrow[\frac16 R_1+R_3]{\frac16R_1+R_2}
	\left[\begin{array}{3} 
		-6 \amp  -7 \amp  46 \amp  77 \\ 
		0 \amp  \frac56 \amp  -\frac73 \amp  -\frac{13}6 \\
		0 \amp  \mathbf{\underline{\frac{11}6}} \amp  -\frac{16}3 \amp  -\frac{31}6
\end{array} \right]
    \xto{R_2:R_3}
	\amp \left[\begin{array}{3}
		-6 \amp  -7 \amp  46 \amp  77 \\ 
		0 \amp  \frac{11}6 \amp  -\frac{16}3 \amp  -\frac{31}6\\
		0 \amp  \frac56 \amp  -\frac73 \amp  -\frac{13}6
\end{array} \right]
	\xto{-\frac5{11}R_2+R_3}
	\left[\begin{array}{3}
		-6 \amp  -7 \amp  46 \amp  77 \\ 
		0 \amp  \frac{11}6 \amp  -\frac{16}3 \amp  -\frac{31}6\\
		0 \amp  0 \amp  \frac1{11} \amp  \frac2{11}
\end{array} \right]

statement.p:
Recall our swamping example. This time we'll use floating-point arithmetic but include partial pivoting.

    \begin{abmc}{2}10.0^{-20} \amp  1.0 \amp  1.0
    1.0 \amp  2.0 \amp  4.0\end{abmc} 
	\xto{R_1:R_2}
	\amp \begin{abmc}{2}
		1.0 \amp  2.0 \amp  4.0
    10.0^{-20} \amp  1.0 \amp  1.0
	\end{abmc}
	\xto{-10.0^{-20}R_1+R_2}
	\left[\begin{array}{2}
		1.0 \amp  2.0 \amp  4.0 \\
		0.0 \amp  1.0 \amp  1.0
\end{array} \right]
